ys in which men, women, and children responded to marital violence. It raises important questions about women’s status within marriage and society, the nature of family life, and the changing ideals and lived realities of the modern marital experience in Ireland.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Ireland.2bisacsh  aDomestic violence.  aFamily violence.  aFeminism.  aHistory of the family.  aIrish society history.  aMarital violence.  aWife beating.1 aDiver, Cara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612012040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526120120423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526120120/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles